Rating: 3
I made this for 4th of July weekend...It was FANTASTIC! The only reason I am not giving it 4 forks is because I made some changes. Like some of the others below, I subbed low-fat buttermilk for heavy cream. I increased the amount of mustard, lemon and pepper. In addition, I used more scallions than called for and added crumbled crispy appledwood bacon. Everyone thought it was delicious ...even my finicky non-potato salad eating husband liked it. Definite keeper!

Rating: 3
I've made this dish a few times now, and it always seems to hit the spot, but only after some substantial modifications. I love the combination of the vegetables and apple, but the dressing definitely needs to be punched up a bit to compete with the heavy cream- I double to triple the mustard, lemon juice, salt, sugar and pepper and once it sits overnight it's heaven! Also, to liven up the color, instead of using parsley I leave the skins on my Gala apples and add extra celery and green onions. Looks good and tastes great too!

Rating: 2
I've tried this recipe twice and both attempts have been unsuccessful. First, who writes a potato salad to serve only 4 people? Potato salad is for potlucks and bbqs, not for a small dinner. Something must be getting lost in having to quadruple this recipe because the flavor is blah. The apples pretty much carry all the flavor.

Rating: 3
This was tasty enough but was wholly unappetizing looking. I minced up some red pepper (radishes might have worked too), and sprinkled generously with pepper - and still had to put it in a bright coloured bowl to make it look good. I might try paprika next time.

Rating: 3
Unique taste, lighter than most potato salads. I used Gala apples for more crunch and low-fat buttermilk instead of cream (double the mustard and lemon juice to compensate). I recommend making it at least a day ahead to let the flavors meld.

Rating: 3
A great recipe. Can substitute low-fat buttermilk for some of the heavy cream to cut the fat. Add more mustard and lemon juice to carry the flavor.

Rating: 3
I made this salad last weekend for a party I was supposed to go to (and ended up not going to), so I have been munching on it all week-I love it! I've been making potato salad for a long time, and was looking for a different and unusual recipe to try. to the person who thought the dressing was too runny-try letting it sit in the fridge for a couple of hours before serving. I too thought that it would end up too runny, but after sitting for a while it ended up being perfect! Will definitely make again!

Rating: 0
To Lisa: No! No! No! Don't use flour to thicken the dressing!!!! The reason it was too runny was that it wasn't whisked long enough. Whisking will create a creamy, thick dressing.

Rating: 3
Very different and delicious. I doubled, almost tripled the recipe and it was the hit of a buffet. I used a bit more lemon juice, extra on the apples while I waited for the potatos to cool. All my neighbors want this recipe!

